The '''Karatos Plague''' was a deadly viral infection that originated from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Concord Dawn/Legends|Concord Dawn]]. Traveling in spores, the virus relentlessly attacked the internal chemistry of its host. Blindness occurred in forty [[Galactic Standard Calendar|minutes]], followed by brain death within an hour. Natives of Concord Dawn were vaccinated against the virus as children, so the aggressiveness of this virus was mostly experienced only by offworlders.<ref name="OS4">[[Jango Fett: Open Seasons 4|''Jango Fett: Open Seasons'' 4]]</ref>

[[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] carried Karatos Plague spores in his armor that he could release when needed. He infected [[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]] with them and offered an antidote dependent on an additional concession, but Dooku used [[Detoxify Poison|his command of the Force]] to cure himself. After invoking the [[Living Force/Legends|Living Force]] to recover, the Sith and the bounty hunter came to a final deal.<ref name="OS4">[[Jango Fett: Open Seasons 4|''Jango Fett: Open Seasons'' 4]]</ref>

